        "created_at": "2017-06-26T23:29:54.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>1975 Heitz Martha\u2019s Vineyard - I brought this as a back-up to a back-up to my latest Marea lunch. Truth be told, I thought it was \u201cjust\u201d the Napa bottling. When lunch spilled over to its fifth hour I decided to open it. Served blind, it was thought to be a top Bordeaux from '82. Still densely colored with only slight bricking. Dark fruits and cedar on the nose. Great depth on the palate. Belies its age. Label stated that it wasn\u2019t bottled until August 1979. Staggering.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
